                    "company": "\u2018SAHTEN\u2019 \u0635\u062d\u062a\u064a\u0646 \u2013 The SkatePal Cookbook",
                    "description": "\u2018SAHTEN\u2019 \u0635\u062d\u062a\u064a\u0646 is a portrait of the current skateboarding scene in Palestine, but told in the form of a cookbook. Featuring recipes from local skaters, their families, shop owners, local heroes, past volunteers, and even by Palestine\u2019s own international master chef: Sami Tamimi (co-founder of OTTOLENGI).\n\nI've been volunteering with SkatePal since 2015 \u2013 predominately as an instructor and and occasional skatepark builder \u2013 and this 184-page book is the result of a need to broaden awareness of the organisation beyond the skateboard community (skaters don't have the $$$). After developing the curation with the SkatePal team, I gathered the majority of material during a 2019 trip to Palestine, then spent 2020 writing, editing, and designing the book.\n\nHit the link below and pick up a copy. 100% of profits help to continue SkatePal's programmes...",
